article.headline: Idaho 75, Hawaii 61
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- Jeff Ledbetter scored 15 points, including four 3-pointers, to lead Idaho to a 75-61 victory against Hawaii on Saturday night. The Vandals (13-10, 6-5 WAC) started slow, but heated up when Stephen Madison hit three 3-pointers in the middle of the first half. Idaho then went on a 15-0 run that allowed them to pull ahead 25-17 with a little more than seven minutes left in the half. Ledbetter sank a pair of 3-pointers to push Idaho on a 13-3 run early in the second half, giving the Vandals a 60-43 lead with 12:19 to play. The Vandals went without a field goal in the final seven minutes, but they made 11 of 13 from the free throw line down the stretch. Vander Joaquim led the Warriors (13-10, 4-7) with 14 points while Joston Thomas added 12. Idaho's Deremy Geiger made a career-high 11 assists.
